Package edu.umn.nlpengine

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Artifact
    A single processing artifact, containing a number of Artifact.getDocuments of text and their associated labels.
    ArtifactSource
    The source of a collection of artifacts to be processed in a pipeline.
    ArtifactTask
    An operation to be run once on every artifact run through the processing pipeline. One instance is created per interface Artifact and ArtifactTask.run is called once per instance.
    ArtifactsProcessor
    Responsible for performing processing on every interface Artifact in the pipeline. Is instantiated once, globally, and ArtifactsProcessor.process
    Document
    A text document and its associated label indices. Implements interface TextRange as the range of the document. Implements interface Metadata with the artifact metadata.
    DocumentTask
    An operation to be run once on one of the interface Document objects on each interface Artifact in the pipeline. One instance is created per interface Artifact and DocumentTask.run is called exactly once per instance.
    DocumentsProcessor
    Responsible for performing processing on a interface Document from every interface Artifact in the pipeline. Is instantiated once, globally, and DocumentsProcessor.process is called for every interface Artifact, potentially from multiple threads. Implementations are responsible for thread-safety in the DocumentsProcessor.process method.
    LabelIndex<T extends Label>
    A collection of labels ordered by their location in text. By default sorts by ascending TextRange.getStartIndex and then ascending TextRange.getEndIndex.
    LabelMetadata
    A annotation that describes some metadata about the label.
    Labeler<T extends Label>
    Used to add labels to the document label indices.
    Metadata
    Metadata associated with an interface Artifact. All interface Document objects on the artifact share the same metadata.
    Runner
    Internal interface for a class responsible for running some process on a pipeline component.
    TextRange
    A location in text. Its indices consistent with String.substring and CharSequence.subSequence
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractArtifact
    An abstract subclass of the interface Artifact interface, used for implementing Artifact in java.
    AbstractDocument  
    AbstractLabelIndex<T extends Label>
    Used to implement interface LabelIndex in Java since default method implementations are not pulled from interfaces in Java.
    AbstractTextRange
    Used to implement interface TextRange in Java.
    DistinctLabelIndex<T extends Label>
    A label index where the labels are distinct i.e. non-overlapping.
    DistinctLabelIndexKt  
    DocumentsKt  
    Label
    A labeled element in text.
    LabelIndicesKt  
    Span
    A location in text without any other associated data.
    StandardArtifact
    A standard implementation of interface Artifact.
    StandardLabelIndex<T extends Label>
    A label index backed by a immutable sorted array of interface TextRange values.
    StandardLabelIndexKt  
    StandardLabeler<T extends Label>
    A standard implementation of interface Labeler which handles the creation of interface LabelIndex instances.
    System  
    SystemModule  
    Systems  
    SystemsModule
